        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 26 at 7:13PM CDT until June 26 at 8:00PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 713 PM CDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from 6 miles northeast of Texline to 10 miles northeast of
Amistad, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to roofs, siding, and trees is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Texline.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Torrential rainfall is occurring with these storms, and may lead to
flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
